BACKGROUND:
@godman-protocols/pact is NOT on npm — it is a local package that does not exist on the server. Do NOT import it. Instead, create a self-contained lib file that inlines the minimal PACT v0.2 HMAC-SHA256 verification logic.

PACT is a trust protocol for AI agent-to-agent delegation. A 'mandate' is a signed JSON object one agent gives to another authorising it to take actions up to a spending cap. The Invoica integration: when a paying agent calls PATCH /v1/invoices/:id/status to settle an invoice, it may optionally include an X-Pact-Mandate header with a signed mandate JSON. The lib verifies the signature and checks the spending cap.

TASK: Create the file backend/src/lib/pact-verify.ts with EXACTLY the content below. Do not add or change anything.

---
FILE: backend/src/lib/pact-verify.ts
